data.description: Beautifully & meticulously updated 3 Bedroom 2 Bath home ideally located off the Echo Trail and Passi Rd, on 5.5 acres of property.  The Lower level entrance & landing have porcelain floors and ledge rock accents. Lower level has 2 BR and a newly updated 3/4 Bathroom, sauna, laundry, pantry, craft room, and lovely new rec room with custom live edge bar & shelving and a free standing wood stove, so perfect for entertaining.  Main level is open with vaulted ceiling & two new sky lights.  The kitchen includes a 6 burner gas cooktop on the large island, w/ granite counters and field stone sides, new appliances including double oven.  Dining room & living room are combined and open to the kitchen, maple floors, free standing new wood burning soapstone stove placed on ceramic tile and accented with a classic field stone chimney.  Off the LR are French doors that enter the office and sliding doors take you out to the generous 9' x 31' upper deck.  The private upper level is an ensuite: master bedroom, walk in closet, full bathroom, and an open space great for yoga or reading/sitting area.  Many new updates and improvements including: shingles, white-pine siding on house & garage, water softener, carpet in lower bedrooms & rec room, water heater & baseboard heat combination from boiler.  Attached 2 stall garage and detached 2 stall all newly: insulated, new propane heaters, and garage doors with automatic openers.  Above the detached garage is a heated & insulated 12 x 25 workout/yoga area.  Features are charming with big beams, laminate floor, and accent runner lights; a fun and inspiring space.  The acreage provides pristine forest surroundings with trails for skiing, 4 wheeling, and recreating on your own land.  Open yard perfect for games & activities, in the winter it's been the home of a large skating rink off of the new 12 x 31 back deck.  Back up generator in place and plumbed to run off of the propane for the unexpected power outages.  This is a beautiful offering with too many unique details to describe, a must see!
